decl: example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f
og_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f := by
  constructor
  · intro h y
    apply h
    apply inverse_spec
    use y
  intro h x1 x2 e
  rw [← h x1, ← h x2, e]
new_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f  := by
  constructor
  · exact fun h y => h (inverse_spec _ ⟨y, rfl⟩)
  · exact fun h x1 x2 e => by rw [←h x1, e, h x2]

decl: example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f
og_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f :=
  ⟨fun h y ↦ h (inverse_spec _ ⟨y, rfl⟩), fun h x1 x2 e ↦ by rw [← h x1, ← h x2, e]⟩
new_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f :=
  ⟨fun h y ↦ h (inverse_spec _ ⟨y, rfl⟩), fun h x1 x2 e ↦ by rw [← h x1, ← h x2, e]⟩

decl: example : Surjective f ↔ RightInverse (inverse f) f
og_raw:
example : Surjective f ↔ RightInverse (inverse f) f := by
  constructor
  · intro h y
    apply inverse_spec
    apply h
  intro h y
  use inverse f y
  apply h
new_raw:
example : Surjective f ↔ RightInverse (inverse f) f    := by
  constructor
  exact fun h y => inverse_spec _ (h y)
  exact fun h y => ⟨inverse f y, h y⟩

decl: theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f
og_raw:
theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f := by
  intro f surjf
  let S := { i | i ∉ f i }
  rcases surjf S with ⟨j, h⟩
  have h₁ : j ∉ f j := by
    intro h'
    have : j ∉ f j := by rwa [h] at h'
    contradiction
  have h₂ : j ∈ S := h₁
  have h₃ : j ∉ S := by rwa [h] at h₁
  contradiction
new_raw:
theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f  := by
  intro f surjf
  let S := { i | i ∉ f i }
  rcases surjf S with ⟨j, h⟩
  have : j ∉ f j ↔ j ∉ S := by rwa [h]
  exact this.2 (this.1 (λ hj, (this.1 hj) hj))
